Sentencas: Nanoscale oxide Ce0.5Zr0.5O2 powder has been prepared by a microwave combustion method as the anode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Characteristic and preparation of Ce0.5Zr0.5O2 as the anode support for solid oxide fuel cells by phase inversion technology

Sentencas: The Ce0.5Zr0.5O2 material has been characterized using X-ray diffraction (XRD), scanning electron microscope (SEM) and the BET method.
Titulo: Characteristic and preparation of Ce0.5Zr0.5O2 as the anode support for solid oxide fuel cells by phase inversion technology

Sentencas: The NiO-Ce0.5Zr0.5O2 anode-supported cells are prepared by phase inversion technique and YSZ electrolyte thin film is obtained by dip-coating.
Titulo: Characteristic and preparation of Ce0.5Zr0.5O2 as the anode support for solid oxide fuel cells by phase inversion technology

Sentencas: The dual-pore structure anode and dense electrolyte are observed by SEM after co-firing process.
Titulo: Characteristic and preparation of Ce0.5Zr0.5O2 as the anode support for solid oxide fuel cells by phase inversion technology

Sentencas: Excellent electrochemical performance of single cell is demonstrated operating on hydrogen (3% H2O), exhibiting the maximum power densities of 218, 342 and 508 mW cm(-2) at 700, 750 and 800 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Characteristic and preparation of Ce0.5Zr0.5O2 as the anode support for solid oxide fuel cells by phase inversion technology

Sentencas: In addition, NiO-Ce0.5Zr0.5O2 anode possess high resistance to carbon deposition, indicating which could be promising candidate anodes for direct hydrocarbon SOFCs.
Titulo: Characteristic and preparation of Ce0.5Zr0.5O2 as the anode support for solid oxide fuel cells by phase inversion technology
